						<div class="postbody">You could also keep all of your code in the fixed 16K bank and only access data and subroutines in the other banks. Many games function like this.
<br />
<br />UxROM really is a handy mapper as 256K should be enough for a lot of types of games. It all depends on the features you need of course. If you find there is something you can't do that you need to, then you might consider getting something more complex. But if you were using NROM, UxROM is perfect. You get both more Code/Data space AND could use more CHR space as you game is no longer limited to 8K of CHR.</div>

